# Account Management Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    Start([Trading Bot Start]) --> Init[Initialize Account Services]

    Init --> SyncService[AccountSyncService]
    Init --> Selector[AccountSelector]

    SyncService --> CheckMT5{MT5 Connected?}

    CheckMT5 --> |Yes| GetInfo[Get MT5 Account Info]
    CheckMT5 --> |No| UseCached[Use Cached Account]

    GetInfo --> Exists{Account Exists in DB?}

    Exists --> |Yes| Update[Update Balance & Equity]
    Exists --> |No| Create[Create New Account Record]

    Update --> Account[TradingAccount Object]
    Create --> Account

    UseCached --> Account

    Account --> Selector

    Selector --> GetActive{Get Active Account}

    GetActive --> Cached{Cached Account<br/>Available?}

    Cached --> |Yes| IsActive{Is Active?}
    Cached --> |No| FirstActive[Get First Active Account]

    IsActive --> |Yes| ActiveAccount[Active Account Ready]
    IsActive --> |No| FirstActive

    FirstActive --> SetCache[Set as Cached]
    SetCache --> ActiveAccount

    ActiveAccount --> Trading[Trading Operations]

    subgraph Trading["Trading Cycle"]
        direction TB
        Generate[Generate Signal] --> Validate[Validate Risk]
        Validate --> Execute[Execute Trade]
        Execute --> LinkPosition[Link to Account]
    end

    LinkPosition --> NextCycle{Next Symbol?}

    NextCycle --> |Yes| Generate
    NextCycle --> |No| PeriodicSync[Periodic Account Sync]

    PeriodicSync --> SyncService

    %% Account Switching
    ActiveAccount -.->|User Request| Switch[Switch Account]
    Switch --> Selector

    %% Styling
    classDef service fill:#e7f5ff,stroke:#1c7ed6,color:#000
    classDef decision fill:#f8f9fa,stroke:#495057,color:#000
    classDef account fill:#d3f9d8,stroke:#2f9e44,color:#000
    classDef trading fill:#fff4e6,stroke:#f4a127,color:#000

    class SyncService,Selector service
    class CheckMT5,Exists,Cached,IsActive,NextCycle decision
    class Account,ActiveAccount account
    class Generate,Validate,Execute,LinkPosition trading
```

## Multi-Account Data Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph MT5["MetaTrader 5"]
        Acc1[Account 1<br/>159394302]
        Acc2[Account 2<br/>123456]
        Acc3[Account 3<br/>789012]
    end

    subgraph Sync["AccountSyncService"]
        Fetch[Fetch Account Info]
        Determine[Determine Type<br/>DEMO/LIVE]
        Upsert[Upsert to DB]
    end

    subgraph DB[(Database)]
        TA[trading_accounts]
        Pos[positions]
    end

    subgraph Select["AccountSelector"]
        GetActive[Get Active]
        Switch[Switch Account]
        ListAll[List All]
    end

    subgraph Bot["Trading Bot"]
        Execute[Execute Trades]
        Track[Track Positions]
    end

    Acc1 --> Fetch
    Acc2 --> Fetch
    Acc3 --> Fetch

    Fetch --> Determine
    Determine --> Upsert
    Upsert --> TA

    TA --> GetActive
    TA --> ListAll

    GetActive --> Execute
    Switch --> Execute

    Execute --> Pos
    Track --> Pos

    Pos -.->|Filter by Account| GetActive
```

## Account Lifecycle

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Unconnected: Bot Start

    Unconnected --> Connecting: MT5 Connect
    Connecting --> Connected: Login Success
    Connecting --> Failed: Login Failed

    Failed --> Unconnected: Retry

    Connected --> Syncing: Initial Sync
    Syncing --> Active: Account Created/Updated
    Syncing --> Inactive: Account Disabled

    Active --> Syncing: Periodic Sync
    Active --> Switching: User Switch

    Switching --> Active: New Account
    Switching --> Inactive: Old Account

    Active --> Disconnected: MT5 Disconnect
    Inactive --> Disconnected: MT5 Disconnect

    Disconnected --> [*]: Bot Stop
